The SA Weather Service is warning of more heavy rains and flooding in many parts of the country. Gauteng's department of Human Settlements says around 500 people have been displaced. Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - The SA Weather Service is warning of more heavy rains and flooding in many parts of the country on Tuesday. READ: Centurion Hotel flooded after heavy rains Gauteng's Department of Human Settlements says around 500 people have been displaced. Some areas in Tshwane experienced flooding as a result of the continuous wet weather conditions. Tshwane emergency services have been rescuing residents from flooded homes and cars in Centurion. SURVIVAL GUIDE: What to do in a flash flood Hundreds of homes have been destroyed in Mamelodi. WATCH: Evacuation underway at Centurion Hotel Emergency services have warned people to avoid low-lying bridges during a flood. Motorists have been warned to avoid roads that are flooded.